---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Team"
  description="We are a family company. Gloria, Julieta, and Miguel — strategy, science, and narrative under one roof."
  lang="en"
  alternateHref="/equipo"
>

  <section class="bg-ocean py-24 lg:py-32 text-sand">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-[1.05] mb-6">
        We are a family company.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-sand/65 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Three disciplines, one table. That's why we can commit to behavioral outcomes,
        not just deliverables.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white border-b border-ink/6 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-ink/35 mb-10">
        How this started
      </p>
      <div class="bg-cream rounded-sm p-6 lg:p-8 text-sm text-ink/60 italic leading-relaxed border border-ink/8">
        [PLACEHOLDER: Company origin story — to be written in Miguel's voice. 2–3 paragraphs.
        Include: how Gloria, Julieta, and Miguel came to combine foresight, behavioral science,
        and creative production under one roof; the specific moment when they realized traditional
        communication fails because it ignores behavior; what makes the family perspective unique.
        Specific, personal, first-person plural.]
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-sand py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-20 lg:space-y-24">

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-20 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[10px] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-accent mb-4">01</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-ocean mb-1">Gloria Sánchez</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/45 italic mb-8">Future Thinking</p>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/65 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            <p>
              Gloria has spent over twenty years working in organizational strategy and foresight
              across Colombia and Latin America. Her specialty is helping companies understand what
              forces are reshaping their industry and what collective behaviors they'll need to
              navigate those changes — before they become urgent.
            </p>
            <p class="bg-cream rounded-sm p-4 text-xs italic text-ink/50 border border-ink/8">
              [PLACEHOLDER: Gloria's personal paragraph — what she cares about, her background,
              why behavior change, what connects her to this work.]
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="bg-ink/8 rounded-sm aspect-[3/4] flex items-center justify-center">
          <figcaption class="text-[10px] text-ink/25 font-mono text-center px-4">[PHOTO: foto_gloria.jpg · 600 × 800 px]</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-20 items-start">
        <figure class="bg-ink/8 rounded-sm aspect-[3/4] flex items-center justify-center order-2 lg:order-1">
          <figcaption class="text-[10px] text-ink/25 font-mono text-center px-4">[PHOTO: foto_julieta.jpg · 600 × 800 px]</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-accent mb-4">02</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-ocean mb-1">Julieta [surname]</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/45 italic mb-8">Behavioral Science</p>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/65 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            <p>
              Julieta is the diagnostic architect at Emerito. Her work starts in the field: observing,
              asking, understanding why people do what they do — not what they say they do. She applies
              the COM-B framework to identify the exact levers an intervention needs to move.
            </p>
            <p class="bg-cream rounded-sm p-4 text-xs italic text-ink/50 border border-ink/8">
              [PLACEHOLDER: Julieta's personal paragraph — background, why behavioral science,
              what connects her to Emerito's work.]
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-20 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[10px] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-accent mb-4">03</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-ocean mb-1">Miguel Zuluaga</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/45 italic mb-8">Creative Content</p>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/65 leading-relaxed text-sm">
            <p>
              Miguel is creative director and producer. His job is to take the behavioral diagnostic
              and turn it into something people actually watch and feel. Character, story, narrative
              architecture, visual direction — the instruments that convert a behavioral science
              finding into a piece that changes what people do.
            </p>
            <p class="bg-cream rounded-sm p-4 text-xs italic text-ink/50 border border-ink/8">
              [PLACEHOLDER: Miguel's personal paragraph — background, why narrative, what connects
              him to behavior-change work, something personal about Medellín or the family.]
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="bg-ink/8 rounded-sm aspect-[3/4] flex items-center justify-center">
          <figcaption class="text-[10px] text-ink/25 font-mono text-center px-4">[PHOTO: foto_miguel.jpg · 600 × 800 px]</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white border-y border-ink/6 py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-ink/35 mb-10">How we work</p>
      <ul class="space-y-5">
        <li class="flex gap-5">
          <span class="text-accent text-lg leading-none flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">·</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Iteration with the client</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 leading-relaxed">We work in short sprints with frequent check-ins. We never disappear for six weeks to come back with something you didn't ask for.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-5">
          <span class="text-accent text-lg leading-none flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">·</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Diagnosis before production</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 leading-relaxed">We don't produce before understanding the problem. That can feel uncomfortable if you already have a video in mind — but it's what makes the result work.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-5">
          <span class="text-accent text-lg leading-none flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">·</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Transparent pricing</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 leading-relaxed">Proposals are clear and detailed. Nothing grows silently. If there's a scope change, we name it before executing it.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-5">
          <span class="text-accent text-lg leading-none flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">·</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Measuring results</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 leading-relaxed">When the client gives us access to field data, we measure. We don't promise metrics we can't control, but we commit to learning from the outcome.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-ocean py-24 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-sand mb-5">Shall we work together?</h2>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="inline-block bg-sand text-ocean text-sm font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-sm hover:bg-cream transition-colors">
        Let's talk →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
